ğŸ§  Explanation:
DISTINCT â†’ Removes duplicate values from the result set and returns only unique entries. This is useful when you want to see a clean list without repetitions.

LIMIT â†’ Controls how many rows are shown. Ideal for previewing a small portion of large tables without loading everything.

These two commands are often used together to quickly review unique data samples from large datasets.
